&lt;p&gt;STIRLING, UK - 31st May 2010: A double decker bus which has been converted into a fully functioning charity shop made its first stop in Stirling today to encourage more people involved in helping out in their local communities as part of Volunteer week, which runs from 1-7th June.  The Big Red Cross Bus will tour the UK and give new volunteers the opportunity to have their first go at volunteering in a charity shop.  Pictured l to r volunteers Heather McLean and Vicky Armour dress manikins outside the shop.   (Photograph: MAVERICK PHOTO AGENCY)&lt;/p&gt;

