&lt;p&gt;ⓒRebecca Bugge, All Rights Reserved&lt;br /&gt;
Do not use without permission.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Polish memorial over those dead at Ravensbrück - this photo was taken on the 1st of September 2009, that is on the day 60 years after the German invasion of Poland. The flowers had just been placed there by a member of the Polish embassy in Berlin. 40000 Polish women and children came to the camp. 8000 of them survived the war.&lt;br /&gt;
