&lt;p&gt;During the Regional Homeland Security Oversight Committee (&lt;a href="http://rhsoc-d.missouristate.edu/" rel="nofollow"&gt;RHSOC&lt;/a&gt;) annual meeting 20 October 2010 at the E-plex in Springfield MO, the public was invited to see a collection of resources including command vehicles, communication vehicles, mass care shelter trailers, &lt;a href="http://www.citizencorps.gov/cert/" rel="nofollow"&gt;CERT&lt;/a&gt; trailers, generators, mobile ham radio units, command busses, fire vehicles, mobile corrals, animal mass care trailers... and this new Red Cross shower and laundry trailer. This self-contained unit has six showers with an &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/ozarksredcross/5099949075/"&gt;ADA compliant shower room&lt;/a&gt; and lift.  (Photo by &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/masscareman" rel="nofollow"&gt;Greg Gaines&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

